                                    "content": ". As indicated by \"RecNet\", each method was combined with a light- field reconstruction network that had the same architecture as RecNet. The network was trained for each imaging method from scratch; the coding patterns and weights in RecNet were jointly optimized on the same dataset as ours. We also used the software of JAEC provided by Mizuno et al. [28], which had 12 times the parameters of our RecNet, and was retrained on the same dataset as ours. Finally, to simulate lens- array based imaging (LA) [1, 2, 31, 32], which can take a light field in a single shot, we down- sampled each view of a light field into the "
